subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greenville,_Alabama
object: Template:Infobox settlementGreenville is a city in Butler County, Alabama, United States. At the 2010 census, the population was 8,135. The city is the county seat of Butler County and is known as the Camellia City. The movement to change the official Alabama state flower from the goldenrod to the camellia originated in Greenville.
